        "client_msg_id": "191c3b72-e90e-422f-ae37-c6a65088d137",
        "text": "The entire `R CMD ...` toolkit assumes one shared library per package, referenced in `NAMESPACE`.  Inaki was trying to make you understand that inside your own code (from that one library) you already can load another shared library [been there, done that] so you can do today what you aim for, and you avoid a (possibly contentious and lengthy) discussion about build systems you do not need ... because you already _can_ do what you want to be possible.",
